  "text": "Related Work. A widely used approach for enhancing fault tolerance is to penalize large values of the parameters by a regularisation func-tion [CITATION_1] ) [CITATION_2] ). Alternatively, constraint optimisation approaches using minimax constraint [CITATION_3] as well as quadratic programming [CITATION_4] can be used for very small networks. Unlike simple regularisation functions, unsupervised pre-training of the initial network layers followed by supervised fine-tuning can significantly enhance the fault tolerance [CITATION_5] . Traditional techniques to enhance reliability such as additional redundancy by adding nodes and synapses (Phatak and Koren 1995) provides partial fault tolerance.",
